name: RadaarTouchResponse
desc: Holds information about touch response in the RadaarTouchResponse.

name: RadaarTouchResponse
desc:
If touch happens, RadarChart processes it internally and passes out a RadaarTouchResponse
that contains a touchedSpot, it gives you information about the touched spot.

name: copyWith
desc:
Copies current RadaarTouchResponse to a new RadaarTouchResponse,
and replaces provided values.

name: touchedSpot
desc: touch happened on this spot. this spot has useful information about spot or entry

name: RadaarTouchedSpot
desc: It gives you information about the touched spot.

name: RadaarTouchedSpot
desc:
When touch happens, a RadaarTouchedSpot returns as a output,
it tells you where the touch happened.
touchedDataSet, and touchedDataSetIndex tell you in which dataSet touch happened,
touchedRadarEntry, and touchedRadarEntryIndex tell you in which entry touch happened,
You can also have the touched x and y in the chart as a FlSpot using spot value,
and you can have the local touch coordinates on the screen as a Offset using offset value.

name: currentStep

Index that is active for the surrounding CustomStepper widget. This may be
different from stepIndex if the user has just changed steps and we are
currently animating toward that step.

name: isActive
desc:
True if the indicated step is also the current active step. If the user has
just activated the transition to a new step, some CustomStepper.type values will
lead to both steps being rendered for the duration of the animation shifting
between steps.

name: onStepCancel

name: onStepContinue
desc: The callback called when the 'continue' button is tapped.

name: stepIndex
desc:
Index of the step for which these controls are being built. This is
not necessarily the active index, if the user has just changed steps and
this step is animating away. To determine whether a given builder is building
the active step or the step being navigated away from, see isActive.

A builder that creates a widget given the two callbacks onStepContinue and
onStepCancel.

name: CustomStepper
desc:
A material stepper widget that displays progress through a sequence of
steps. Steppers are particularly useful in the case of forms where one step
requires the completion of another one, or where multiple steps need to be
completed in order to submit the whole form.

name: CustomStepper
desc: Creates a stepper from a list of steps.

name: controlsBuilder
desc: The callback for creating custom controls.

name: createState
desc: Creates the mutable state for this widget at a given location in the tree.

name: currentStep
desc: The index into steps of the current step whose content is displayed.

name: elevation
desc: The elevation of this stepper's Material when type is CustomStepperType.horizontal.

name: margin
desc: custom margin on vertical stepper.

name: onStepCancel
desc: The callback called when the 'cancel' button is tapped.

name: onStepContinue
desc: The callback called when the 'continue' button is tapped.

name: onStepTapped
desc:
The callback called when a step is tapped, with its index passed as
an argument.

name: physics
desc: How the stepper's scroll view should respond to user input.

name: steps
desc: The steps of the stepper whose titles, subtitles, icons always get shown.

name: type
desc:
The type of stepper that determines the layout. In the case of
CustomStepperType.horizontal, the content of the current step is displayed
underneath as opposed to the CustomStepperType.vertical case where it is
displayed in-between.

name: values
desc: A constant List of the values in this enum, in order of their declaration.

name: Step
desc:
A material step used in CustomStepper. The step can have a title and subtitle,
an icon within its circle, some content and a state that governs its
styling.

name: Step
desc: Creates a step for a CustomStepper.

name: content
desc: The content of the step that appears below the title and subtitle.

name: isActive
desc: Whether or not the step is active. The flag only influences styling.

name: label
desc:
Only CustomStepperType.horizontal, Optional widget that appears under the title.
By default, uses the bodyText1 theme.

name: state
desc:
The state of the step which determines the styling of its components
and whether steps are interactive.

name: subtitle
desc:
The subtitle of the step that appears below the title and has a smaller
font size. It typically gives more details that complement the title.

name: title
desc: The title of the step that typically describes it.
